Driehaus Capital Management, Inc., headquartered in Chicago, Illinois, is an investment management firm specialising in U.S. and international aggressive growth stocks. The firm offers a wide range of products, including managed accounts and mutual funds, and the firm currently offers one hedge fund, Driehaus Long/Short Advantage Fund, an equity hedge fund which began in April of 2001. These products are targeted toward the high-net-worth individual and institutional market segments. The firm has $2.7 billion under management. 

To achieve exceptional performance over time, Driehaus Capital Management, Inc. utilises aggressive growth investing, a proven investment discipline that seeks to maximise returns by investing in high-potential growth companies. The firm's investment philosophy is that revenue and earnings growth are the principal factors in determining common stock prices over the long term. Only through sustained earnings growth can dividends be raised, book values increased, and cash flows expanded. Stocks are selected based on fundamental and technical criteria. Indicators of positive fundamental criteria include accelerating sales and earnings growth rates, strong operating statistics, positive earnings surprises, and upward estimate revisions as well as high earnings quality, attractive industry or country developments and positive changes in the investment environment. Positive technical criteria include price and volume breakouts, good relative strength and increasing institutional interest. 

The firm was founded by Richard H Driehaus in 1982. Mr Driehaus is the CEO, Chairman of the firm and Chief Investment Officer, as well as one of the Portfolio Managers for the firm's Small Cap Growth and Mid Cap Growth products. He is widely regarded within the investment industry as an expert in the area of aggressive growth investing. Mr Driehaus is the architect of the firm's investment philosophy and has primary responsibility for the firm's domestic investment process. In early 2000, he was named to  Barron's "All-Century" team of the 25 individuals who have been most influential within the mutual fund industry over the past 25 years. Mr Driehaus is also the CEO and Chairman of Driehaus Securities Corporation, an affiliated broker-dealer he founded in late 1979. 







